1 enga ging programs that inspire curiosity, creativity, and informed
2 inquiry; and
3 WHEREAS, librarians and library professionals are highly trained
4 individuals who guide users in accessing, evaluating, and using
5 information effectively, helping to develop critical thinking and
6 information literacy skills necessary for success in school, work,
7 and civic life; and
8 WHEREAS, libraries uphold the fundamental principles of
9 intellectual freedom as protected by the First Amendment, ensuring
10 access to a broad range of viewpoints and ideas without censorship;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, libraries strengthen communities by supporting early
13 childhood development, family engagement, workforce readiness, and
14 lifelong education, contributing to an informed and literate
15 society; and
16 WHEREAS, recognizing and supporting libraries and library
17 professionals is essential to maintaining vibrant, inclusive, and
18 knowledgeable communities throughout the State of Oklahoma;
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
20 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
21 THAT the month of April 2026 is hereby designated as Library
22 Month in the State of Oklahoma, in recognition of the invaluable
23 contributions of libraries and library professionals to literacy,
